Ames.Delta Upsilon Chapter House: Founded on November 4, 1834 at Williams College in Williamstown, Massachusetts, Delta Upsilon (ΔΥ) is the sixth, all-male, college Greek-letter organization founded in North America (only Kappa Alpha Society, Sigma Phi, Delta Phi, Alpha Delta Phi, and Psi Upsilon predate). It is popularly and informally known as "DU" or "Delta U" and its members are called "DUs". Although historically found on the campuses of small New England private universities, Delta Upsilon currently has over 76 chapters across the United States and Canada.
